# Idleon Helper — architecture for agents

Full reference: `docs/agent-architecture.md` and root `AGENTS.md`.

## Flow

Renderer uses **`window.api` only** (preload). Main handles **`ipcMain.handle`** in `src/main/handlers.ts`. Low-level automation from main uses **`backendCommand`** in `src/main/backend/backend-command.ts`, which sends WebSocket messages via `sendCommand` in `backend-client.ts` to **`ws://localhost:5000/ws`**.

Do not open WebSockets or call `sendCommand` from the renderer.

## Adding a new IPC feature

Update together: `src/preload/index.ts`, `src/preload/index.d.ts`, `src/main/handlers.ts`. Prefer implementing behavior under `src/main/scripts/` (or appropriate main module).

## WebSocket command names (C#)

`find`, `findWithDebug`, `click`, `drag`, `dragRepeat`, `stop`. Types: `src/main/backend/backend-types.ts`. Dispatch: `backend/Handlers/MessageHandler.cs`.

## Scripts vs UI navigation

- **Renderer pages:** Zustand `NavigationPage` in `src/renderer/src/store/navigation.ts`, sidebar in `app-sidebar.tsx`, `pageMap` in `app.tsx` — no React Router.
- **In-game UI automation:** `src/main/scripts/navigation/` (used by main-process scripts, not exposed as IPC unless you add it).
